post.title: Reflecting on 2015, The Tech Academy
post.description: Since we are approaching the end of this year, we decided to briefly reflect on what occurred in 201
post.content:
Since we are approaching the end of this year, we decided to briefly reflect on what occurred in 2015 for our school. And here it is:

-2015 saw the largest student body and highest number of graduates in history. For just a couple examples, there are now Tech Academy graduates working at: Jive Software, Monsoon and Disney (yes, that Disney). We have maintained our 100% placement rate of graduates for another year!

-Our curriculum was updated in keeping with ever-changing technology. This included launching the program on a fully custom-made online Learning Management System. Courses are able to be accessed online from anywhere in the world. Students learn seven in-demand programming languages, making us one of the most comprehensive boot camps in existence. 

-Due to growth, we have doubled our total campus size and upgraded the premises. If you haven’t been by in several months, you should come check it out!

All-in-all, 2015 has been our most successful year by leaps and bounds. We feel honored to help people break into this industry and thereby improve the well being and their life.

As the Co-Founders of the school, we are very thankful and proud of our employees who are a key aspect of our continued success.

Here's to 2016, the next best year ever!

Jack Stanley & Erik Gross
